✅ Create Your First HTML File Using VS Code
Open VS Code
Click File → New File
Save the file as index.html or filename.html
If you installed the Live Server extension, right-click on the file → Open with Live Server Or just open the file manually in a browser (double-click index.html)

✅HTML file in notepad
Open notepad
Type your code
Save it as index.html or "filename".html
Then double click the file from your File Explorer
The web browser will open displaying your HTML output


